-{"id":"bd-18d8","title":"Add CSI/DCS sequence length limits (DoS prevention)","description":"## Problem

src/input/parser.rs lines 129-141 and src/terminal/queries.rs lines 169-179 scan for sequence terminators without bounds:

```rust
// parser.rs - CSI parsing
while end < input.len() {
    let b = input[end];
    if (0x40..=0x7e).contains(&b) {
        break;
    }
    end += 1;  // Scans entire input!
}

// queries.rs - DCS parsing  
let st_pos = input[content_start..]
    .windows(2)
    .position(|w| w == b"\x1b\\")  // Scans entire input!
```

## DoS Potential

A malicious terminal could send:
- Very long CSI: \x1b[ followed by 1MB of digits (no terminator)
- Very long DCS: \x1bP followed by 1MB of data (no ST terminator)

This causes O(n) scanning on every parse() call until the sequence is complete or the application gives up.

## Required Fix

Add maximum sequence length constants:

```rust
const MAX_CSI_LENGTH: usize = 256;   // Reasonable for any real sequence
const MAX_DCS_LENGTH: usize = 4096;  // Larger for DCS content

// In CSI parsing
if end - 2 > MAX_CSI_LENGTH {
    return Err(ParseError::SequenceTooLong);
}

// In DCS parsing
if input.len() - content_start > MAX_DCS_LENGTH {
    return Err(ParseError::SequenceTooLong);
}
```

## Considerations

- Real CSI sequences are typically <50 bytes
- Real DCS sequences (e.g., Sixel) can be larger but still bounded
- Document the limits in public API
- Consider making limits configurable for special applications

## Priority

P2 - Defense-in-depth, unlikely to be exploited in typical use

## Files to Modify

- src/input/parser.rs: CSI and DCS parsing loops
- src/terminal/queries.rs: DCS response parsing","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-28T23:06:34.918480210Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-28T23:06:34.925894150Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-18d8","depends_on_id":"bd-2qib","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-28T23:06:34.925853414Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
